By many measures, it is thriving: its jobless rate is just 5.5 percent compared with the U.S. rate of 7.6 percent; it has a diverse employer base; and private business investment is robust, totaling $579 million in 2012, more than double a 10-year average, according to the Birmingham Business Alliance.
